tafsir[5]{c,v,t}:
  99,5,"Because Allah will have taught it and commanded it to do so."
  100,1,"Allah takes an oath on the horses that run so hard that their breath can be heard."
  100,3,"And He also takes an oath on the horses that raid the enemy at dawn."
  100,4,"And unsettle the dust by their running."
  100,5,"They then take their riders collectively into the midst of the enemy."